latestPosts.caption:
Very very easy Republic Day Nailart ft. @hisugarpop 🇮🇳

This was inspired by @dramatickle.error 🌸

This technique is called “Drag Marble Nailart”. You need to super fast while doing these nails because regular polishes trend to dry very soon. So, keep all your bottles open and be ready before the polish starts to dry.😂

I personally don’t like this technique bcs it takes very long to dry 😭 But the designs are too good 🌸🥰

[ Drag Marble Nails, Nailart, Nails, Republic Day Nails, Freehand Nailart ]

For all my Pink Girlies 🌸 Here is the perfect shade for Valentines Day 🎀

It is a textured shade, feels coarse after drying. You can always apply a top to smoothen that out. 

If you are someone who doesn’t like texture then this is not the shade for you. ✨

[ Nails, Lace Noir, Polish Swatch, Swatch, 2025 ]

🎄✨ Nail Art Fest 3 ✨🎄

Showcasing my Christmas-themed nail art set inspired by techniques taught by our masters:
	1.	Thumb: A 3D reindeer 🦌 with a snow globe ❄️ on top, bringing the festive spirit to life.
	2.	Index Finger: Elegant jewelry 💎 on a nude base, enhanced with a mesmerizing green aurora effect.
	3.	Middle Finger: Opal Nail Art as the base, topped with a 3D wreath 🎀 for a magical holiday vibe.
	4.	Ring Finger: A one-stroke Christmas tree 🎄 accented with caviar beads, all on a shimmering Cateye base.
	5.	Little Finger: Stacked gifts 🎁 near a window, paired with a soft grey and white ombré base for a cozy winter feel.

With this design, I aimed to keep the art wearable and practical, ensuring it’s not only beautiful but also realistic for anyone who wish to try 3D nails without compromising on functionality.

A heartfelt thank you to all the masters for teaching these incredible techniques, which made this creation possible! 🙏✨

Also, a huge shoutout to @spillnailpolishes for helping me with the snow globe as I did not have builder gel to do it. 😭 Thankyou Nikkie 🥹❤️
